#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:1
msgid "Introduce the implicit vtkStridedArray: a strided view on a buffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:3
msgid ""
"The `vtkStridedArray` is a `vtkImplicitArray` providing a strided view on an "
"existing memory buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:5
msgid ""
"If you work with a multi-dimensional buffer of data, you can create a "
"`vtkStridedArray` to manipulate a single dimension (that can be itself a "
"scalar or a vector) of this buffer through the classical `vtkDataArray` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:9
msgid ""
"This is typically useful in the InSitu context as with the "
"`vtkConduitSource` for Catalyst. In this case, we want to create "
"`vtkDataArray` around existing memory with zero copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:13
msgid "Let's have this buffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:14
msgid ""
"std::vector<float> localBuffer\n"
"{\n"
"      0, 1000, 2000, 3000,\n"
"      1, 1001, 2001, 3001,\n"
"      2, 1002, 2002, 3002,\n"
"      3, 1003, 2003, 3003,\n"
"      4, 1004, 2004, 3004,\n"
"      5, 1005, 2005, 3005,\n"
"      6, 1006, 2006, 3006,\n"
"      7, 1007, 2007, 3007,\n"
"      8, 1008, 2008, 3008,\n"
"      9, 1009, 2009, 3009\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:29
msgid ""
"This may represent a one-component array (first column) interlaced with a 3-"
"components array, both with 10 tuples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:31
msgid "We can now create a `vtkStridedArray` as follow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:32
msgid ""
"  vtkNew<vtkStridedArray<float>> stridedArray;\n"
"  stridedArray->SetNumberOfComponents(3);\n"
"  stridedArray->SetNumberOfTuples(10);\n"
"  stridedArray->ConstructBackend(\n"
"    localBuffer.data(), /*stride*/ 3, /*offset*/ 1, /*components*/ 3);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:39
msgid ""
"This will provide a (zero copy) view on the last 3 columns of our initial "
"buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:41
msgid ""
"In the context of `CatalystConduit`, with the same buffer we can write the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:42
msgid ""
"  fields[\"vectorArray/values/x\"].set_external(\n"
"    localBuffer.data(), nbPts, /*offset=*/sizeof(float), stride * "
"sizeof(float));\n"
"  fields[\"vectorArray/values/y\"].set_external(\n"
"    localBuffer.data(), nbPts, /*offset=*/sizeof(float) * 2, stride * "
"sizeof(float));\n"
"  fields[\"vectorArray/values/z\"].set_external(\n"
"    localBuffer.data(), nbPts, /*offset=*/sizeof(float) * 3, stride * "
"sizeof(float));\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.6/strided-array.md:51
msgid ""
"The conduit source will then provide a `vtkStridedArray` as in previous "
"example."
msgstr ""
